From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Apr 2026 06:15:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Import native-FX quantized Linear, shape, and builtin arith

Native-FX quantized attention graphs still surface several standard FX forms
that the importer did not handle robustly:
- quantized Linear and LayerNorm modules as call_module targets
- Tensor.shape captured through builtin getattr/getitem
- Tensor methods view/transpose/contiguous
- builtin arithmetic such as truediv after dequantize

Bridge these onto standard Torch ops. Quantized module outputs now inherit
quantized tensor metadata from their inputs, quantized Linear lowers through
torch.quantized.linear_unpack, vararg view dimensions are materialized as
torch.list<int>, quantized weights are rebuilt from int_repr via
aten._make_per_tensor_quantized_tensor, and getitem learns how to unpack those
shape lists even when FX metadata omits val entries for quantized nodes.
---
 python/torch_mlir/extras/fx_importer.py | 221 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++----
 1 file changed, 203 insertions(+), 18 deletions(-)

diff --git a/python/torch_mlir/extras/fx_importer.py b/python/torch_mlir/extras/fx_importer.py
index 346c95d..3b0744c 100644
